//*[starts-with(text(), 'text')] - equals to beginning of the phrase

//*[text()='text'] - equals to exact text


We can use contains:

Contains will help us to find element 
based on partial text/value regardless of location.

//*[contains(text(), 'text')]

//*[contains(@title, 'value')]

(//button)[n] - nth element of matching
//button[n] - nth child

To go to parent element: use  /..

Example:
from the text to parent element
//*[text()='text']/.. 